cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG

This paper proposes a new gaze-based interface for web browsing, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also uses a probabilistic model to infer the likelihood of selecting different hyperlinks, which involves computer vision (cs.CV), information retrieval (cs.IR), and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper evaluates different methods for varying the dwell times, which could involve machine learning (cs.LG).
